<?xml version="1.0"?>

<!--
  List of available levels.
  Each level properties should be mostly self-explanatory, see TLevel
  properties documentation if in doubt.

  - default_available_for_new_game is optional attribute.
    Default value is "false", which means that the level is initially
    not available for the player (when he chooses "New Game" from menu).
    Practically, default_available_for_new_game should be "true" only
    for the starting game level.

  - implementation_class is also optional attribute.
    Default value is "TLevel", which means that the level will be
    handled with vanilla TLevel implementation.
    Many advanced tricks are possible by implementing in the game code
    (CastleLevelSpecific unit) a descendant class of TLevel that does
    something special, then you should set this attribute to the name
    of that class.

  - _sound attributes: you can use here a name from ../sounds/index.xml

  - TODO: planned, when "Debug menu" will show that will be useful:
    octree_max_depth, octree_max_leaf_items_count:
    octree generation parameters. Default value is -1,
    and it means that the default values in VRMLTriangleOctree unit
    (see e.g. [http://vrmlengine.sourceforge.net/apidoc/html/VRMLTriangleOctree.html]
    or just look in the sources) will be used.

    It's adviced to use these options only if you see a real difference
    in FPS between "real" FPS and "rendering" FPS. This may mean that
    AI and collision detection take a long time, and this may be cured
    by a better octree parameters. You can control these parameters at runtime
    from "Debug menu", so it's most comfortable to first test your parameters
    using "Debug menu" and then write them to this file.

    For educational purposes, you can make an experiment and set
    octree_max_depth = 0: this forces a one-leaf tree, effectively
    making octree searching work like a normal sequence searching.
    You should see dramatic loss of game speed. Look at FPS: while
    the rendering speed will stay the same, the "real" FPS will
    drow down, since AI and collision detection will eat a lot of CPU.

  - loading_bg: filename of image file to display while loading the
    level (under the progress bar). Optional.
  - loading_bar_y_position: between 0 and 1, indicates position
    of progress bar when loading level. Should be synchronized
    with loading_bg image, to look right. Optional, default value
    is 0.5 which simply means "middle of the screen".

  Rest of the attributes is required.
  Filenames are specified relative to directory of this XML file.
  As path delimiter use slash "/".
-->

<levels
  demo_level_name="gate_demo">

